</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1238,1330,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1238,1330,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
reaching couplet # 
<quantity box="[256,313,185,211]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[320,549,185,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976)</bibRefCitation>
key. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Maldonado, 1976" authorityName="Maldonado" authorityYear="1976" box="[945,1351,185,211]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubromarga">
<emphasis box="[945,1145,185,211]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza rubromarga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[1153,1351,185,211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">
Maldonado, 
<quantity box="[1295,1351,185,211]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0190399999999995" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" unit="in" value="1976.0">1976</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in possessing a taller median process of the pygophore with sinuate lateral margins. The recurved apical fold also is narrower than the base in the new species. Despite being characterized as having only the first connexivum spined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[151,364,289,316]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, W. F." box="[378,527,289,315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="71 - 73" refId="ref8432" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1900) Hymenoptera, Hemiptera Heteroptera, Homoptera, Neuroptera, and Orthoptera. In: Report on a collection made by Messrs. F. V. McConnell and J. J. Quelch at Mount Roraima in British Guiana. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 8 (2), pp. 71 - 73." type="journal article" year="1900">Kirby (1900)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirby, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[652,1000,289,315]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis box="[652,837,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza perarmata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirby, W. F." box="[853,991,289,315]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="71 - 73" refId="ref8432" refString="Kirby, W. F. (1900) Hymenoptera, Hemiptera Heteroptera, Homoptera, Neuroptera, and Orthoptera. In: Report on a collection made by Messrs. F. V. McConnell and J. J. Quelch at Mount Roraima in British Guiana. The Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 8 (2), pp. 71 - 73." type="journal article" year="1900">Kirby, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as having “Abdominal segments with four small lateral spines on the basal half”; thus, I have concluded that Maldonado misidentified 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1228,1379,325,350]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis box="[1228,1379,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. perarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[383,536,359,384]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perarmata">
<emphasis box="[383,536,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. perarmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Maldonado" box="[571,793,359,385]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="403 - 433" refId="ref8630" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1976) The genus Heza (Hemiptera: Reduviidae). Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 60 (3), 403 - 433. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 60 i 3.10533" type="journal article" year="1976">Maldonado’s (1976</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 51–52) treatment still differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swanson" authorityYear="2021" box="[1248,1366,359,384]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graziae">
<emphasis box="[1248,1366,359,384]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. graziae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the median process of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">
The general habitus of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lichtenstein, 1796)" baseAuthorityName="Lichtenstein" baseAuthorityYear="1796" box="[459,877,428,455]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippium">
<emphasis box="[459,642,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza ephippium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lichtenstein, A. A. H." box="[657,869,428,455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" refId="ref8590" refString="Lichtenstein, A. A. H. (1796) Catalogus musei zoologici ditissimi Hamburgi, d. III. Februar 1796 auctionis lege distrahendi. Sectio Tertia. Continens Insecta. Schniebes, Hamburg, 224 pp." type="book" year="1796">Lichtenstein, 1796</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1859" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[933,1192,428,455]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[933,1071,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">Heza similis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[1078,1192,428,455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" pagination="175 - 204" refId="ref8807" refString="Stal, C. (1859) Till kannedomen om Reduvini. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 16 (10), 175 - 204." type="journal article" year="1859">Stål, 1859</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
looks similar, but the armature of the anterior pronotal lobe of those species is medium-sized and apically blunted and the short, robust, truncate median process of the pygophore differs markedly in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[848,955,497,523]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Heza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[848,955,497,523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="370">H. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
